			"Duration": "See below",
			"Save": "Negates",
			"Description": "<p>When this spell is cast, the wizard can cause a single overwhelming sensation to fill the minds of the subject creatures. Each victim is allowed a Save to resist.</p><p>The <em class=\"spellname\">Instilled Emotion</em> overwhelms any opposite effect from the same spell, and also from any similar spell of 4th level or below.</p><p>The caster can choose which <em class=\"spellname\">Emotion</em> to create when casting the spell, from the following:</p><dl class=\"detailed\"><dt>Courage<sup>*</sup></dt><dd>The affected creatures are filled with an overwhelming bravery. They fight with a +2 bonus To Hit, +2 damage, and can continue to act while between 0 and -5 HP. The recipients will not retreat or take defensive actions, but do know friend from foe. This spell counters (and is countered by) <em>Fear</em>.</dd><dt>Fear<sup>*</sup></dt><dd>The affected creatures flee in panic, and are likely to drop whatever they are holding when struck by the spell; the base chance of dropping items is 60% at 1st level / HD, -5% per lvl / HD over. It counters (and is countered by) <em>Courage</em>.</dd><dt>Despair<sup>*</sup></dt><dd>The affected creatures submit to the demands of any opponent: surrender, get out, etc. Otherwise, the creatures are 25% likely to do nothing in a round, and 25% likely to turn back or retreat. It counters (and is countered by) <em>Hope</em>.</dd><dt>Elation<sup>**</sup></dt><dd>The affected creatures are filled with a feeling of complacent well-being, adding +3 to all <em>reaction rolls</em> and making attack unlikely, unless the creatures are subject to extreme provocation. It counters (and is countered by) <em>Melancholy</em>.</dd><dt>Harmony<sup>**</sup></dt><dd>The affected creatures become full of affection and understanding for all nearby. Any friendly action causes <em>reaction rolls</em> at a +3 bonus. It counters (and is countered by) <em>Hatred</em>.</dd><dt>Hatred<sup>**</sup></dt><dd>The affected creatures become full of anger and loathing for all nearby. Any adverse action causes a <em>reaction roll</em> at a -3 penalty. It counters (and is countered by) <em>Harmony</em>.</dd><dt>Hope<sup>*</sup></dt><dd>The affected creatures are filled with a good and noble feeling. This raises morale, Save rolls, To Hit rolls, and damage caused by +2. It counters (and is countered by) <em>Despair</em>.</dd><dt>Melancholy<sup>**</sup></dt><dd>The affected creatures are filled with dismay and a tendency toward maudlin introspection. This emotion penalizes <em>Surprise</em> rolls by -2 and adds +2 to initiative rolls. It counters (and is countered by) <em>Elation</em>.</dd></dl><p class=\"note\"><sup>*</sup> Duration is 3d4 rounds.</p><p class=\"note\"><sup>**</sup> Duration is 6d4 rounds.</p>"
