	{
		"title": "Marvellous Looking Glass",
		"level": 6,
		"school": "Divination",
		"type": "Astral",
		"Casting Time": "1 hour",
			"Range": "Within the Mundane Realm",
			"AOE": "One target creature",
			"Duration": "10 minutes / caster level",
			"Save": "None",
			"Description": "<p>This powerful magic is an improved version of <em class=\"spell\">Magic Mirror</em>, and operates in a similar way. It allows the caster to first scry on, and then make contact with, a far distant creature or place, by peering through the Astral Realm.</p><p>Like <em class=\"spell\">Magic Mirror</em>, it requires a looking glass of finely wrought and highly polished silver that costs at least 100 gp.</p><p>The chance of success is as shown below. Any failure prevents a second attempt upon the same subject or location for 1 day.</p><h5>Base chance:</h5><dl class=\"complex-terms\"><dt>Scryer is very familiar with subject/place</dt><dd>45%</dd><dt>Scryer is familiar with subject</dt><dd>35%</dd><dt>Scryer knows subject slightly</dt><dd>20%</dd><dt>Scryer knows subject only by name</dt><dd>10%</dd></dl><h5>Modifiers:</h5><dl class=\"complex-terms\"><dt>Each level of the scryer</dt><dd>+5%</dd><dt>Scryer uses subject's <em>True Name</em></dt><dd>+50%</dd><dt>Scryer has fragment of subject's body</dt><dd>+50%</dd><dt>Scryer has subject's familiar</dt><dd>+50%</dd><dt>Scryer has object owned by subject</dt><dd>+20%</dd><dt>Scryer has image of subject</dt><dd>+10%</dd><dt>Subject is hiding in a village</dt><dd>-10%</dd><dt>Subject is hiding in a town</dt><dd>-20%</dd><dt>Subject is hiding in a city</dt><dd>-30%</dd><dt>Subject is underground</dt><dd>-25%</dd><dt>Subject is insane or <em class=\"spell\">Enfeebled</em> </dt><dd>-40%</dd><dt>Subject is magically altered (<em class=\"spell\">Shapeshift</em>ed, etc.)</dt><dd>-35%</dd></dl><p>The <em class=\"spellname\">Looking Glass</em> cannot locate a creature under <em class=\"spell\">Forlorn Encystment</em>.</p><p>A successful roll allows the caster to both see and hear the creature or location, from a fixed point of view. This point of view is usually 8 ft. in the air, tilted downwards, but can appear at any height off the ground if the caster desires.</p><p>Once established, the following spells can be easily cast via the <em class=\"spellname\">Looking Glass</em>:</p><ul><li><em class=\"spell\">Cat's Eye</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Comprehend Language</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Tongues</em></li></ul><p>The following spells have a 5% chance / caster level of operating correctly through the mirror:</p><ul><li><em class=\"spell\">Detect Arcane Magic</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Detect Good or Evil</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Speak On The Wind</em></li></ul><p>The <em class=\"spellname\">Marvellous Looking Glass</em> may cause observed creatures to feel a nagging sense of being spied upon. The base chance of this happening is equal to the subject's Int as a percentage, modified as follows:</p><dl class=\"complex-terms\"><dt>Each Level / HD</dt><dd>+5%</dd><dt>Subject originates from another Realm</dt><dd>+25%</dd></dl><p><em class=\"spellname\">Marvellous Looking Glass</em> also allows the caster to plunge his hands through the mirror and make contact with the target.</p><p>He can strike with a one-handed weapon, try to strangle a creature, or grab and bring back any small object that will fit within his grasp. He can only reach out to his arms' length from the fixed viewpoint of the mirror, which may be easy for a target to avoid.</p><p>The caster cannot use a touch spell or cast spells while his hands are through the <em class=\"spellname\">Looking Glass</em>, and will take appropriate damage from any injury to his hands or arms. The caster can pull his hands back to safety as a movement action, and try again on subsequent rounds.</p>"
	},
