			"Range": "Touch",
			"AOE": "Semicircle 30 ft. radius",
			"Duration": "Permanent",
			"Save": "None",
			"Description": "<p>This spell enchants a greenish chrysoberyl of at least 10gp value to store either an image, or spoken words.</p><p>The spell is cast upon the stone, excepting one of the two possible command words, which are delayed until the spell is activated.</p><p>Anyone holding <em class=\"spellname\">The Panoptic Gem</em> may speak one of the command words, which then captures either an image of the area immediately in front of it, or else all words spoken in the next ten breaths, depending on which command is used.</p><p>Once an image or speech has been captured, anyone holding the <em class=\"spellname\">Gem</em> need only speak the same word to make the stone either dimly show the image within, or whisper the words it holds.</p><p>A single <em class=\"spellname\">Gem</em> can only hold one image or a dozen words, but will retain them forever, unless the stone is destroyed.</p>"
