		"Casting Time": "6",
			"Range": "20 ft.",
			"AOE": "One target / round",
			"Duration": "One round / three caster levels; see below",
			"Save": "See below",
			"Description": "<p><em class=\"spellname\">Paramount Gaze</em> enables the caster to meet the eyes of a creature and intone a single word to cause a powerful effect.</p><p></p><p>The power in the wizard's <em class=\"spellname\">Gaze</em> can be used once / round for the duration of the spell. In later rounds, after the first, the caster can move and take other non-combat actions in addition to making a <em class=\"spellname\">Gaze</em> attack, but cannot cast other spells.</p><p>This spell does not affect sightless creatures, undead of any type, or extend beyond the Realm occupied by the caster.</p><p>The wizard selects one of four possible effects at the time the spell is cast, and this effect cannot be changed in later rounds. Any <em class=\"spellname\">Gaze</em> is negated by a successful Save. The four possible effects of the spell are as follows:</p><dl class=\"detailed\"><dt>Agony</dt><dd>This <em class=\"spellname\">Gaze</em> causes sudden pain and fever to sweep over the subject's body. The victim suffers a penalty of -3 on all rolls, and moves at half normal rate. The subject remains stricken for 10 minutes / caster level. The effects cannot be negated by healing spells, but a <em class=\"spell priest\">Lift Curse</em>, <em class=\"spell\">Remove Curse</em> or a successful <em class=\"spell\">Dispel Arcane Magic</em> will be effective. Non-humanoid creatures Save with +2 bonuses.</dd><dt>Dominion</dt><dd>This <em class=\"spellname\">Gaze</em> allows the wizard to <em>charm</em> a single person or monster. The victim becomes absolutely loyal to the caster, even to the point of personal danger. Non-humanoid creatures Save with +2 bonuses. The effect lasts for 3d6 hours.</dd><dt>Terror</dt><dd>This <em class=\"spellname\">Gaze</em> causes the subject to flee in blind terror for 3d4 rounds. After this the creature refuses to face the caster, and if subsequently confronted by them either cowers, or bolts for the nearest cover (50% chance of either). The latter effect lasts 10 minutes / caster level. This attack can be negated by spells that counter fear.</dd><dt>Torpor</dt><dd>This <em class=\"spellname\">Gaze</em> causes the target to fall into a comatose slumber, unless the subject successfully Saves. Only targets who normally require sleep can be affected. An affected creature must be shaken or otherwise shocked back to consciousness; otherwise they will sleep for 1d6 hours.</dd></dl><p>This magic is believed to have its origins in an ancient inhuman power, from whom the sorcerors of the First Kingdom learned.</p>"
	},
	{
		"title": "Part Water",
		"level": 6,
		"school": "Alteration",
		"type": "Elemental",
		"Casting Time": "10 rounds",
			"Range": "60 ft. / caster level",
			"AOE": "3 ft. deep x 90 ft. wide x 60 ft. long, / caster level",
