	{
		"title": "Pentacle, Great",
		"level": 6,
		"school": "Conjuration",
		"Casting Time": "1 hour, plus see below",
			"Range": "30 ft.",
			"AOE": "See below",
			"Duration": "Up to 1 year / caster level; see below",
			"Save": "Negates; see below",
			"Description": "<p>To cast this spell is to attempt a dangerous act: luring a powerful creature from another Realm to a prepared trap, where it will be held until it agrees to perform a service. The type of creature to be snared must be known and stated during the casting.</p><p>The spell requires the caster to have already created the restraining ward. The ward can occupy an area of at least 10 ft. x 10 ft., to a maximum of 30 ft. x 30 ft., and cannot be interrupted by any kind of solid object.</p><p><em class=\"spellname\">Great Pentacle</em> opens a portal within the Realm of the target creature, and brings it to their attention. They can resist the summons with a Save, modified if the caster uses their <em>True Name</em>.</p><p>If the Save succeeds, the creature ignores the opening, and the spell fails. If it succeeds by 6 or more, they may learn of the identity of the would-be trapper, and later exact retribution. If the Save fails, the creature steps into the opening and is drawn into the <em class=\"spellname\">Pentacle</em>.</p><p>A <em class=\"spellname\">Great Pentacle</em> may also fail at the moment of arrival of its occupant; the chance is as follows:</p><ul><li>A hand-drawn <em class=\"spellname\">Pentacle</em> using mundane chalk, paint or the like takes 10 minutes to create, and has a base chance of failure of 20%. If it is drawn over a longer period of time, using specially prepared pigments, the chance of breaking free is reduced by 1% for every extra hour. This can bring the base chance to 5%; the minimum for a hand-drawn ward. The rare and expensive pigments cost 10gp per extra hour spent drawing.</li><li>An inlaid or carved design will require one week of work by the caster and cost 100gp, with a base chance of failure of 10%. It can be improved by using inlays of onyx and True Lead, and oils of angelica and garlic. Each 1% improvement will cost an additional 50gp and require an additional week of work. This can bring the base chance of failure to 0.</li></ul><p>A <em class=\"spellname\">Pentacle</em> that fails has no power over its intended victim.</p><p>A being caught in a <em class=\"spellname\">Great Pentacle</em> cannot pass through its lines, nor use magic or other supernatural abilities on anything outside it. It will be able to throw missiles across the ward, so by tradition the inside of the <em class=\"spellname\">Pentacle</em> is kept bare of objects.</p><p>Only the summoner can enter the <em class=\"spellname\">Pentacle</em> without breaking it. Any other interruption of the ward will render it useless - this includes creatures entering the bounded regions, a straw laid across the lines, or an object thrown into the area from outside.</p><p>Once safely trapped, the caster can offer bribes, use promises, or make threats in order to exact one service from the captive creature. It will usually resist such a service, with a score that begins as being equal to its Wisdom +3. This score drops by 1 for each month that the captive remains within the <em class=\"spellname\">Pentacle</em>.</p><p>The DM will assign a value to what the wizard has said to the trapped creature, rating it from 0 to 5 (with 5 being the most persuasive). This rating is then subtracted from the resistance score of the creature. If the creature rolls a successful 2d10 check against this score, it refuses the service. New offers can be made, or the old ones offered again, once each month.</p><p>However, a creature will never agree to an impossible or completely unreasonable demand.</p><p>This can be repeated until the creature promises to serve, until it breaks free, until the duration expires, or until the caster decides to free it.</p><p>Once a single service is completed, the creature only needs to inform the caster to be instantly returned whence it came. The creature might later seek revenge.</p><p>If a captive is freed by the caster without completing a service, it will immediately be able to attack, flee or perform any action it wishes.</p><p>Instead of bargaining with the captive, the caster can choose to use <em class=\"spell\">The Spell Of Binding</em> to doubly imprison it. Breaking the <em class=\"spellname\">Binding</em> does not necessarily free the subject from the <em class=\"spellname\">Great Pentacle</em>; the combined results will depend on the method of <em class=\"spellname\">Binding</em> used.</p>"
	},
	{
		"title": "Permanency",
		"level": 8,
		"school": "Metamagic",
		"Casting Time": "10 minutes",
			"Range": "See below",
			"AOE": "See below",
			"Duration": "Permanent",
			"Save": "None",
			"Description": "<p>This powerful spell can be used to make other castings last forever, or else as part of the enchantment of a magical item.</p><p>If used to extend the duration of a spell, <em class=\"spellname\">Permanency</em> must be cast before the spell, and within its normal range. There are several sets of spells that <em class=\"spellname\">Permanency</em> is known to work upon; magics that affect the caster, magics that affect other creatures or objects, and magics that only affect an object or area. Other applications may be possible, but researching such will take time and effort; see below.</p><p>A successful <em class=\"spell\">Dispel Arcane Magic</em> cast upon a spell made <em class=\"spellname\">Permanent</em> will suppress the effect for 2d6 rounds. A <em class=\"spell\">Mordenkainen's Disjunction</em> will remove both the spell and the <em class=\"spellname\">Permanency</em>.</p><p>The following can made <em class=\"spellname\">Permanent</em> when used on the caster:</p><ul><li><em class=\"spell\">Aegis Against Blades</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Aegis Against Missiles</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Assume Evanescent Semblance Of Smoke</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Aura Of Protection</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Box Of Flesh</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Cat's Eyes</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Charm Of Untiring Nourishment, The</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Comprehend Language</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Deep Pockets</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Detect Arcane Magic</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Detect Invisibility</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Essence Of Life</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Detect Scrying</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Detect Undead</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Mantle Of Influence</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Taptine's Eldritch Occultation</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Tongues</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Unseen Servant</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Ward Off Cantrips</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Ward Off Slumber</em></li></ul><p>The following can made <em class=\"spellname\">Permanent</em> when used on the caster, another creature or an object:</p><ul><li><em class=\"spell\">Cloak Of Banality</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Echoes In The Skull</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Enlarge</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">False Trail</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Glamour</em> (and the reverse)</li><li><em class=\"spell\">Gust Of Wind</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Invisibility</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Mage's Armour</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Mage's Armour, Greater</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Magic Mouth</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Melisande's Light Step</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Mark The Soul</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Purulent Waft</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Sigil Of Armouring</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Sight Through Empty Sockets</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">The Charm Of Forgetfulness</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Voice From The Skull</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Wizard Eye</em></li></ul><p>The following can made <em class=\"spellname\">Permanent</em> when used on an object or area:</p><ul><li><em class=\"spell\">Alarum</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Audible Glamer</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Bar Passage</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Calling The Leaden Gloom</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Dancing Lights</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Dweomer's Vessel</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Fire Gate</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Flying Chattel</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Fragile Egg</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Grasp Of Death</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Grasp Of Earth</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Grasp Of Stone</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Grease</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Guards And Wards</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Haunting</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Host Of Watchful Eyes</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Imperative Script</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Nacreous Coil</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Open The Way</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Prismatic Sphere</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Rope Trick</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Shackle Undead</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Shrunken Token</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Sovereign Amulet</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Tenser's Floating Disc</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Tenser's Greater Floating Disc</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Umbral Cat</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Undead Mount</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Voriax's Iron Sack</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Wall Of Darkness</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Wall Of Fire</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Wall Of Obdurate Force</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Wall Of Ice</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Ward Against Etheric Intrusion</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Ward Against Teleportation</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Ward Against The Undead</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Web</em></li><li><em class=\"spell\">Web Of The Cunning Ones</em></li></ul><p>The DM <em>may</em> allow other spells to be made <em class=\"spellname\">Permanent</em>. Researching this possible application costs as much time and money as independently researching the selected spell itself.</p><p>Each spell made <em class=\"spellname\">Permanent</em> ages the caster by 5% of their usual lifespan.</p><p>Using <em class=\"spellname\">Permanency</em> as part of the creation of a magic item is discussed under the ritual To Enchant A Wondrous Item. This casting does not age the wizard, but may instead reduce their Constitution.</p>"
	},
	{
		"title": "Phandaal's Mantle Of Stealth",
		"level": 4,
		"school": "Illusion",
		"Casting Time": "4",
			"Range": "Touch",
			"AOE": "One recipient",
			"Duration": "4 rounds + 1 round / caster level",
			"Save": "See below",
			"Description": "<p>This spell is similar to <em class=\"spell\">Invisibility</em>, making the recipient undetectable by normal or <em>Night Vision</em>. By using the <em class=\"spellname\">Mantle Of Stealth</em>, however, the recipient is able to attack or cast spells and remain unseen.</p><p>Items dropped or put down by the <em>invisible</em> creatures become visible; objects picked up disappear, if they can be hidden away beneath clothing. Carried light sources are not affected, and will seem to float unsupported.</p><p>Invisible creatures <em>Surprise</em> others at a -3 penalty.</p><p>Attacks against <em>invisible</em> creatures suffer a -4 penalty To Hit.</p><p>Telltale noise, footprints and other traces can allow an opponent to sense an <em>invisible</em> creature. These traces are only noticeable when actively looked for within 10 ft.; a Save vs. Perception at a -4 penalty will allow the opponent to detect them. If successful, the <em>invisible</em> creature can be attacked at a lesser penalty of -2, until able to disengage and move away.</p>"
	},
	{
