	{
		"title": "Pulkmous' Refulgent Thunderhead",
		"level": 3,
		"school": "Conjuration",
		"type": "Elemental",
		"Casting Time": "5",
			"Range": "Caster only",
			"AOE": "30 ft. radius",
			"Duration": "2 rounds / caster level",
			"Save": "See below",
			"Description": "<p>This magic causes winds to gather around the caster, and his surroundings to darken. This effect builds up throughout the Casting Time, becoming a cloud of rumbling, buffeting winds and moist air lit by leaping sparks, which remains around the caster as he moves.</p><p>All melee combat within the cloud suffers from -2 penalties To Hit, unless combatants are able to see in shadowy conditions. Missile fire into or out of the <em class=\"spellname\">Thunderhead</em> is at a -3 penalty To Hit, due to the strong winds.</p><p>All within the <em class=\"spellname\">Thunderhead</em>, except the caster, must Save every round or suffer 1d4 damage from the sparks that shoot through it. Creatures bearing a great deal of metal Save with a -3 penalty.</p><p>Gale force winds or <em class=\"spell priest\">Mastery Of Vapours</em> can disperse the <em class=\"spellname\">Thunderhead</em> after two rounds.</p>"
