	{
		"title": "Purulent Waft",
		"level": 2,
		"school": "Conjuration",
		"type": "Elemental",
		"Casting Time": "2",
			"Range": "90 ft.",
			"AOE": "10 ft. radius",
			"Duration": "1 round / caster level; see below",
			"Save": "Negates",
			"Description": "<p>When <em class=\"spellname\">Purulent Waft</em> is cast, the wizard summons a billowing mass of nauseous vapours, which seeps from the ground and will sicken breathing creatures caught within it. The mass remains static, roiling within the AOE.</p><p>Any creature caught within the miasma must Save, or be left reeling for 1d4+1 rounds, even after leaving the <em class=\"spellname\">Waft</em>. Failure applies a penalty of -2 to all rolls, a penalty of +2 AC, and forces them to make <em>Concentration</em> rolls in order to cast spells. Those who make successful Saves can leave the vapours without suffering any ill effects, although those remaining must continue to Save each round.</p><p>These poisonous effects can be slowed or neutralised by appropriate magic. The <em class=\"spellname\">Purulent Waft</em>'s duration is halved in a moderate breeze and is dispersed in one round by a stronger one, such as a <em class=\"spell\">Gust Of Wind</em>.</p><p>This spell has also been referred to as <em class=\"spellname\">Charnel Breath Of The Pit</em>.</p>"
