			"Save": "See below",
			"Description": "<p>This spell creates magical runes affecting creatures that pass over, touch, read them, or pass through a portal upon which the glyphs are inscribed.</p><p>If the substance into which the mark is inscribed is destroyed, the <em class=\"spellname\">Sigil</em> loses all power. For that reason, a caster will usually choose to place the runes on a durable surface. In order to function, a <em class=\"spellname\">Sigil</em> cannot be concealed or covered.</p><p>The type of <em class=\"spellname\">Great Sigil</em> present cannot be recognised without being read, and thus activating its effects. However, all such marks will contain the personal rune of the caster, which might be recognisable by survivors. The caster can choose one of the following effects to place:</p><dl class=\"detailed\"><dt>Death</dt><dd>One or more creatures, whose total HP do not exceed 80, are slain. No Save is allowed.</dd><dt>Discord</dt><dd>Victims fall to loud bickering and arguing; there is a 50% probability that creatures of different alignments attack each other. The bickering lasts for 5d4 rounds, the fighting for 2d4 rounds. No Save is allowed.</dd><dt>Fear</dt><dd>This symbol creates an extra-strong <em class=\"spell\">Know Fear</em> effect, causing victims to Save with -4 penalties to the die roll, or panic and flee for 1d4 rounds / caster level. Those affected are likely to drop whatever they are holding when struck by the spell; the base chance of dropping items is 60% at 1st level / HD, -5% per lvl / HD over.</dd><dt>Hopelessness</dt><dd>Victims must Save or turn back in dejection. Affected creatures will submit to forceful demands from any opponent, including orders to surrender or leave. The hopelessness lasts for 3d4 x 10 minutes; during this period it is 25% probable that affected creatures take no action during any round, and 25% likely that those taking action turn back or retire from battle, as applicable.</dd><dt>Insanity</dt><dd>One or more creatures whose total HP do not exceed 120 become insane, acting as if a <em class=\"spell\">Sow Confusion</em> spell had been placed upon them for 3d6 rounds. No Save is allowed.</dd><dt>Pain</dt><dd>Victims must Save or be afflicted with wracking pains shooting through their bodies, causing a -2 penalty to Dexterity and a -3 penalty to attack rolls for 2d4 days.</dd><dt>Sleep</dt><dd>Victims under 8+1 HD immediately fall into a catatonic slumber and cannot be awakened without injury for 1d12+4 x 10 minutes. No Save is allowed, but only creatures that normally require sleep are affected.</dd><dt>Stunning</dt><dd>One or more creatures whose total HP do not exceed 160 are stunned and reeling for 3d4 rounds, suffering -3 To Hit, -2 AC and dropping anything they are holding. No Save is allowed.</dd></dl><p>A <em class=\"spellname\">Great Sigil</em> cannot be <em class=\"spell\">Erased</em>, and <em class=\"spell\">Dispel Arcane Magic</em> will not remove one. Only a successful <em class=\"spell\">Mordenkainen's Disjunction</em> or <em class=\"spell\">Petty Wish</em> spell can safely do so.</p>"
