			"Description": "<p>This spell summons a Ethereal guardian to protect the AOE. The <em class=\"spellname\">Spectral Guard</em> will wait in abeyance until the condition of its activation is fulfilled, whereupon it will appear and attempt to slay all creatures in the area.</p><p>The spell functions when specific visual or aural conditions are fulfilled within the AOE, according to the command of the caster. Conditions can be as general or as detailed as desired. Some examples are:</p><ul><li>appear when 'the first creature enters the area'</li><li>or 'when the first creature speaks in Dwarvish'</li><li>or 'when the first creature says \"Mirabar\"'</li></ul><p>The <em class=\"spellname\">Guard</em> is a slim ghostly figure whose lower half always tapers away into nothingness, of indeterminate race, bearing an ornate blade.</p><h5>Statblock</h5><dl class=\"statblock\"><dt class=\"name\">name</dt><dd>Spectral Guard</dd><dt class=\"hd\">hd</dt><dd>10d8</dd><dt class=\"hp\">hp</dt><dd>Casters' x 3</dd><dt class=\"initmod\">init</dt><dd>-1</dd><dt class=\"ac\">ac</dt><dd>0, +1 weapon to injure</dd><dt class=\"thaco\">thaco</dt><dd>11</dd><dt class=\"attacks\">attacks</dt><dd>Two attacks 2d6</dd><dt class=\"mv\">mv</dt><dd>40 ft.</dd><dt class=\"xp\">xp</dt><dd>6000</dd><dt class=\"notes\">notes</dt><dd><p>Immune to Mind-affecting spells, has <em class=\"spell\">Second Sight</em></p><p>Able to pass through solid objects and attack Ethereal beings</p><dd></dl><p>It cannot leave the area it guards, and once it has slain all present (or is destroyed) it fades away to nothingness and the spell ends.</p><p>Only one <em class=\"spellname\">Spectral Guard</em> may occupy a given area. The caster can always dismiss it at will.</p><p>The origins of this spell are believed to predate the rise of Man's kingdoms.</p>"
	},
