		"Casting Time": "See below",
			"Range": "30 ft.",
			"AOE": "One skeleton or zombie / caster level; see below",
			"Duration": "Permanent",
			"Save": "None",
			"Description": "<p>When a wizard casts this spell, he imbues animated skeletons and zombies under his control with limited intelligence. The spell gives these undead the ability to speak, in order to answer questions, respond to simple situations, shout warnings, or make introductions.</p><p>This spell affects a maximum of one undead / caster level, granting each a single task to perform or phrase to speak. Alternatively, a given <em class=\"spellname\">Lackey</em> can perform more than one task, but counts multiple times against the limit.</p><p>A task can be as simple as opening a door when visitors arrive, or as complex as cooking a specific dish, each taking no more than an hour to perform. The tasks are short routines that are performed either daily, when a certain situation arises, or when the proper commands are given.</p><p>It takes ten minutes for this spell to affect each creature. Once the spell is cast, the <em class=\"spellname\">Lackeys</em> need no monitoring, except for commands required to start the performance of specific tasks.</p>"
