			"Duration": "1 round / caster level",
			"Save": "None",
			"Description": "<p>When <em class=\"spellname\">Unfortunate Twin</em> is cast by the wizard, he creates an illusory double at the same time that he is cloaked by <em class=\"spell\">Phandaal's Mantle Of Stealth</em>.</p><p>The wizard is then free to go elsewhere, while his double acts independently. The spell enables the illusion of the wizard to speak and gesture as if it were real, and there are full olfactory and touch components as well. The double cannot cast spells, but it may enter combat, although all injury it inflicts is <em>Subdual</em> Damage, which heals quickly and cannot kill. At the most, injuries from a <em class=\"spellname\">Twin</em> may render a target unconscious.</p><p><em class=\"spellname\">The Unfortunate Twin</em> does not require Concentration to be maintained.</p><p>An active and successful attempt to <em>Disbelieve</em> will allow an observer to realise that the double is a fake, and mean that they cannot be injured by it. Any previous injury sustained, once a <em>Disbelief</em> is successful, will immediately fade away.</p>"
