			"Range": "30 ft. / caster level",
			"AOE": "One zombie or skeleton",
			"Duration": "10 minutes / caster level",
			"Save": "None",
			"Description": "<p>This spell is similar to the spell <em class=\"spell\">Speech A'Bounding</em>, in that it allows the caster to throw his voice. However, the caster's voice issues only from the mouth of a specified undead zombie or a skeleton. The undead need not be under the control of the caster for this spell to function, but must be within line of sight when it is cast.</p><p>Once it takes effect, <em class=\"spellname\">Voice From The Skull</em> will continue even if the undead creature moves out of sight of the caster, as long as it remains within range.</p><p>The voice will be a scratchy, raspy whisper not identifiable as the caster's.</p><p>Some attribute the origins of this spell to one <em>Anarazel</em>, a mysterious figure from ages past.</p>"
