			"Duration": "10 minutes/ caster level",
			"Save": "None",
			"Description": "<p><em class=\"spellname\">Wings Of The Spectre</em> creates a great ghostly set of pinions, appearing in mid-air next to the caster.</p><p>They are intangible to everything except their cargo - people and objects of a weight up to 100 lbs / caster level, who can climb aboard them. Their flight is especially stable - passengers may fight and cast spells from the back of the <em class=\"spellname\">Wings</em> as though they were standing on solid ground.</p><p>The <em class=\"spellname\">Spectral Wings</em> have a flight speed of 100 ft. / round, but cannot fly in a space too small for their wingspan of 30 ft.</p><p>Only the caster can command the <em class=\"spellname\">Wings</em>, and only if he is touching them. If not given a command the <em class=\"spellname\">Wings</em> will continue to perform their current action, possibly crashing into anything in their path.</p>"
