	{
		"title": "Wizard's Curse, Greater",
		"level": 4,
		"school": "Enchantment",
		"type": "Curse, Hag-Magic",
		"Casting Time": "1 hour",
			"Range": "1 mile",
			"AOE": "One target creature",
			"Duration": "1 year and 1 day",
			"Save": "Negates",
			"Description": "<p>This spell can only be cast if the wizard possesses an object intimately linked with the victim; a lock of hair, nail clipping, beloved possession or similar, which is burned to bring on the <em class=\"spellname\">Curse</em>. The victim can resist the effect with a Save.</p><p>This spell is the most powerful <em class=\"spellname\">Wizard's Curse</em>. The particular effect on the victim is chosen by the caster from the list below:</p><dl class=\"detailed\"><dt>Cadaver's Curse</dt><dd>Over a few days the victim becomes pale, sickly and haggard, with sunken eyes. They develop a horrible stench which sickens all around. They lose 8 Cha for the duration and suffer -2 to all physical rolls.</dd><dt>Curse of Plagues</dt><dd>Overnight the victim becomes the carrier of a virulent sickening disease. They suffer -2 to all rolls, and may infect all nearby (although those infected do not themselves become carriers).</dd><dt>Curse of Enemies</dt><dd>The victim becomes convinced that all around are plotting his downfall. They will become estranged from allies; Save vs. Wisdom to behave in a friendly fashion to anyone.</dd><dt>Curse of Years</dt><dd>Overnight, the victim loses 1 from Str, Dex, Con and Cha as they become wizened and aged. Their hair will whiten and thin, and their skin become mottled and liver-spotted.</dd></dl><p><em class=\"spell priest\">Detect Evil</em> and wizardly <em class=\"spell\">Detect Arcane Magic</em> will reveal the curse's presence. A <em class=\"spell priest\">Lift Curse</em>, <em class=\"spell\">Remove Curse</em> or <em class=\"spell\">Lift Wizard's Curse</em> will remove the spell effect.</p><p>A victim may bear only one <em class=\"spellname\">Wizard's Curse</em> (of any of the three kinds) from a particular wizard at a time.</p><p>The origins of this spell are said to predate the rise of Man's kingdoms.</p>"
	},
