			"Duration": "1 week",
			"Save": "Negates",
			"Description": "<p>This spell can only be cast if the wizard possesses an object intimately linked with the victim; a lock of hair, nail clipping, beloved possession or similar, which is burned to bring on the <em class=\"spellname\">Curse</em>. The victim can resist the effect with a Save.</p><p>When cast, this spell causes a minor misfortune to haunt the target, chosen by the caster from the list below:</p><dl class=\"detailed\"><dt>Curse of Misfortune</dt><dd>The victim suffers bad luck at all games of chance, or in mundane situations where luck is involved</dd><dt>Curse of Unsightliness</dt><dd>Overnight the victim becomes bald, gains a squint, loses three teeth, or grows several large and painful boils (caster's choice). Cha drops by 2 for the duration.</dd><dt>Cripple's Curse</dt><dd>This version partially withers or twists one limb, giving the victim a -1 on all rolls involving that limb.</dd><dt>Curse of Beasts</dt><dd>The victim gains the unwanted attention of a type of small mundane animal, such as flies, cats or mice (caster's choice). They will be drawn to him and follow him around, often making noise or irritating his companions</dd></dl><p><em class=\"spell priest\">Detect Evil</em> and wizardly <em class=\"spell\">Detect Arcane Magic</em> will reveal the curse's presence. A <em class=\"spell priest\">Lift Curse</em>, <em class=\"spell\">Remove Curse</em> or <em class=\"spell\">Lift Wizard's Curse</em> will remove the spell effect.</p><p>A victim may bear only one <em class=\"spellname\">Wizard's Curse</em> (of any of the three kinds) from a particular wizard at a time.</p><p>The origins of this spell are said to predate the rise of Man's kingdoms.</p>"
