		"Save": "None",
		"Description": "<p>The spell allows the priest to use a pool of clear, still water as a scrying device. The waters become similar to a <em>crystal ball</em>. The caster is not able to scry upon other Realms via a <em class=\"spellname\">Reflecting Pool</em>.</p><p>The chance of success is as shown below. Any failure prevents a second attempt upon the same subject for 1 day.</p><h5>Base chance:</h5><dl class=\"complex-terms\"><dt>Scryer is very familiar with subject</dt><dd>45%</dd><dt>Scryer is familiar with subject</dt><dd>35%</dd><dt>Scryer knows subject slightly</dt><dd>20%</dd><dt>Scryer knows subject only by name</dt><dd>10%</dd></dl><h5>Modifiers:</h5><dl class=\"complex-terms\"><dt>Each level of the scryer</dt><dd>+5%</dd><dt>Scryer has fragment of subject's body</dt><dd>+50%</dd><dt>Scryer has object owned by subject</dt><dd>+20%</dd><dt>Scryer has image of subject</dt><dd>+10%</dd><dt>Subject is hiding in a village</dt><dd>-10%</dd><dt>Subject is hiding in a town</dt><dd>-20%</dd><dt>Subject is hiding in a city</dt><dd>-30%</dd><dt>Subject is underground</dt><dd>-25%</dd><dt>Subject is under <em class=\"spell\">Forlorn Encystment</em></dt><dd>-45%</dd><dt>Subject is insane or affected by <em class=\"spell\">Elruss' Enfeeblement Of The Cognate Mind</em></dt><dd>-40%</dd><dt>Subject is magically altered (<em class=\"spell\">Shapeshift</em>ed, etc.)</dt><dd>-35%</dd></dl><p>The caster can attempt to cast the following spells cast through the <em class=\"spellname\">Reflecting Pool</em>, with a 5% / caster level chance that they function:</p><ul><li><em class=\"spell priest\">Detect Divine Influence</em></li><li><em class=\"spell priest\">Detect Poison</em></li><li><em class=\"spell priest\">Detect Snares And Pits</em></li></ul><p>There is always a chance for the subject to realise that they are being scryed upon. This is equal to the subject's Int as a percentage, modified as follows:</p><dl class=\"complex-terms\"><dt>Subject's Level or HD</dt><dd>+2%</dd><dt>Subject originates from another Realm</dt><dd>+25%</dd></dl><p>A successful roll will indicate that the subject has a strong nagging feeling of being watched; they will usually take action.</p>"
